UCSF (a sprawling medical center on "Pill Hill") has a network of tunnels under the streets there.  I quickly learned to use the "system" to avoid  the hazards of traffic and weather, so I could get PhysDau to appointments, the orthotics lab, and to and from the parking garage in record time.  It was great.  It never occurred to me that it could have been called a SUBWAY!

